I"¥<p><a href="https://directreadout.sci.gsfc.nasa.gov/?id=dspContent&amp;cid=68">IPOPP (the International Polar Orbiter Processing Package)</a>
is a free software used to process raw hdf satellite data from Suomi National
 Polar orbiting Partnership(SNPP), Aqua, and Terra missions. It generate tiff
 and png files contains sst, chlor_a, crefl_rgb files form those raw data.</p>

<h2 id="how-to-install-ipopp">How to install IPOPP</h2>
<!--break-->
<p>To install ipopp, you can follow the following steps:</p>

<ol>
  <li>Create user ipopp.</li>
  <li>Download ipopp from nasa.</li>
  <li>You need to register an account with nasa</li>
  <li>Download downloader_ipopp_2.5.sh</li>
  <li>Run it on your linux machine, make sure you have enough space.</li>
  <li>Uncompress DRL-IPOPP_2.5.tar.gz to ~/IPOPP of ipopp user.</li>
  <li>Run system_test.sh in ~/IPOPP, make sure all tests are passed except the
 database test. IPOPP 2.5 includes standalone mariadb and do not required
 pre-installed database.</li>
  <li>Run install_ipopp.sh</li>
</ol>

